title: Authorizes the superintendent of insurance to phase in certain health insurance rate increases
summary: Authorizes the superintendent of insurance to phase in certain health insurance rate increases; provides that if an increase is fifteen percent or more, the superintendent may phase in the percentage amount which exceeds fifteen percent over a period not to exceed six months.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the insurance law, in relation to permitting the superintendent of insurance to phase in certain increases in premiums for nonprofit medical and dental indemnity on health and hospital service corporations
